            <h3>
                Jameis QB1?
            </h3>
            <iframe src="https://giphy.com/embed/7oOiJugXeC8e0Iq6Kq" width="480" height="480" frameBorder="0" class="giphy-embed" allowFullScreen></iframe>
            <p>
                <a href="twitter.com/adamschefter/status/1431237587302297604?s=21">Jameis Winston</a> has won the starting job in New Orleans which should bring joy to all
                Alvin Kamara drafters. Taysom Hill will still be involved, but it sounds like NO will go for a more traditional passing attack rather than trusting their
                gadget QB with the offense. With Michael Thomas out with an injury for the first few weeks (and possibly more if there truly are issues between he and the front
                office), Alvin Kamara should see a significant bump.
            </p>
            <br>
            <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Jameis Winston has been named the Saints&#39; starting quarterback and will make his first start for New Orleans on opening day vs. Green Bay Packers, per sources.</p>&mdash; Adam Schefter (@AdamSchefter) <a href="https://twitter.com/AdamSchefter/status/1431237587302297604?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 27, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
            <br>
            <h3>
                JK Dobbins Out for the Year
            </h3>
            <p>
                <a href="https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/32107877/baltimore-ravens-jk-dobbins-having-mri-expectation-rb-season-sources-say">JK Dobbins</a> tore his ACL while
                being tackled in the third and final preseason game of the NFL season. Both Gus Edwards and newly annointed #2 Ty'Son Williams should trend upward with Dobbins' departure.
                You should be fading Justice Hill as he is allegedly on the line of being cut.
            </p>
            <br>
            <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Beat confirms Ty&#39;Son Williams is Ravens RB2 <a href="https://t.co/diTL5KJ5GZ">https://t.co/diTL5KJ5GZ</a> <a href="https://t.co/kFt3t1wDuL">pic.twitter.com/kFt3t1wDuL</a></p>&mdash; NBC Sports EDGE Football (@NBCSEdgeFB) <a href="https://twitter.com/NBCSEdgeFB/status/1432330529882271747?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 30, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
            <br>
            <p>
                Do be careful with Ravens running backs in PPR leagues. Lamar Jackson has only thrown 40 times to a running back in his three years in the NFL. You have been warned.
            </p>
            <p>
                Also worth noting that Todd Gurley is still a free agent. However...
            </p>
